{{self-published|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox company | name = Bottecchia Cicli S.r.l. | logo = Bottecchia-logo.jpg | logo_size = 200px | foundation = {{Start date|1924}} | founder = [[Ottavio Bottecchia]] | location = V.le E. Ferrari 15/17 30014 [[Cavarzere]] VE, Italy | industry = [[Bicycle]] manufacturing | products = Bicycles | homepage = {{URL|http://www.bottecchia.com}} }}
[[File:Honig SNeirynck 4JDD2010 1.JPG|thumb|200px|A Bottecchia model]] '''Bottecchia Cicli S.r.l.''' is a [[bicycle]] manufacturing company headquartered in [[Cavarzere]], Italy. They offer about 70 models that include [[Road bicycle|road]], [[Mountain bike|mountain]], [[Trekking bicycle#Trekking bike|trekking]], [[European city bike|city]], [[BMX bicycle|BMX]], [[Folding bicycle|folding]], [[Cyclo-cross#Bicycles|cyclo-cross]], and [[Electric bicycle|electric]]. Some high-end [[Bicycle frame|frames]] are produced in Italy, the rest in Asia, and all the bikes are assembled in Italy. They have distribution in Europe, Australia, Japan, and the United States. They are the technical sponsor of the [[Androni–Sidermec–Bottecchia|Androni-Sidermec-Bottecchia]] professional Italian team,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bottecchia.com/en/news-eventi-en/7771|title=BOTTECCHIA BECOMES THIRD OFFICIAL SPONSOR OF THE ANDRONI SIDERMEC BOTTECCHIA TEAM! {{!}} Reparto Corse|website=www.bottecchia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-14}}</ref>
==History== Bottecchia is a historical bicycle company that started as a small cyclery of Carnielli and improved in 1924 by [[Ottavio Bottecchia]]. A new company with a new name "Bottecchia" was born after the death of [[Ottavio Bottecchia]] in 1926. In 1940 the work force of Bottecchia was 100 people and the company became an outstanding race firm with the historical name of Ottavio Bottecchia and under the management of the Carnielli family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bottecchia.com/en/azienda/storia|title=HISTORY {{!}} Reparto Corse|website=www.bottecchia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-14}}</ref>
They were the technical sponsor of the [[Acqua & Sapone]] professional Italian team, which rode the [[Giro d'Italia]] on Bottecchia SP9s in 2010 and on Bottecchia Emme 2s in 2011.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Lennard Zinn|date=June 7, 2011|title=Technical FAQ|url=http://velonews.competitor.com/2011/06/bikes-and-tech/technical-faq/lennard-zinn-technical-faq-tubular-v-tubeless-for-the-pros-getting-that-special-bike_177569|journal=VeloNews|accessdate=2011-11-18}}</ref>
==Bicycle manufacture== Until now Bottecchia makes a lot of [[Racing bicycle|race]] frames. The company also produces bikes for daily purposes and bicycle parts named "BTC" used only internally. The race profile of the company, is recently imported in the trekking line ("tempo libero") by offering a carbon trekking bike for daily use.
