'''Frederick Robert Flatman''' (1843 – 21 September 1911) was a New Zealand Member of Parliament of the [[New Zealand Liberal Party|Liberal Party]] for the [[Pareora (New Zealand electorate)|Pareora]] and [[Geraldine (New Zealand electorate)|Geraldine]] electorates.

==Early life==
Flatman was born in [[Suffolk]] and went to school in [[Oulton Broad]]. He came to [[Lyttelton, New Zealand|Lyttelton]] on the ''Mary Ann'' in 1862 and went to South Canterbury. He was a successful businessman, and was storekeeper in [[Geraldine, New Zealand|Geraldine]] and [[Woodbury, New Zealand|Woodbury]], and a sawmiller, before he concentrated on farming.<ref name="NZETC Flatman">{{cite book|title=The Cyclopedia of New Zealand : Canterbury Provincial District|year=1903 |url= http://www.nzetc.org/tm/scholarly/tei-Cyc03Cycl-t1-body1-d6-d90-d1.html#name-422984-mention |author=Cyclopedia Company Limited|accessdate=25 May 2010|location=Christchurch |chapter=Geraldine}}</ref><ref>''The New Zealand Liberals: The Years of Power, 1891–1912'' By David Hamer (1988, Auckland University Press, Auckland), p.&nbsp;362</ref>

==Member of Parliament==
