The '''French Society of Financial Analysts''' ({{lang-fr|Société Française des Analystes Financiers (SFAF)}}) is the main professional organisation representing members of the [[France|French]] financial industry. It was created in 1961<ref>{{cite news |title=La SFAF veut incarner la nouvelle diversité de l'analyse financière |url=http://search.lesechos.fr/archives/2006/LesEchos/19699-171-ECH.htm?xtor=AL-4001 |work=[[Les Échos (France)|Les Échos]] |date=30 June 2006 |accessdate=28 March 2010 }}</ref> and currently has over 1500 members, all of whom are financial professionals ([[financial analyst]]s, [[Investment management|portfolio managers]], [[investment banker]]s...etc.). SFAF is a member of [[EFFAS]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Alain Cazalé : La formation conditionne la déontologie |url=http://search.lesechos.fr/archives/2004/LesEchos/19197-159-ECH.htm?xtor=AL-4001 |work=[[Les Échos (France)|Les Échos]] |date=9 July 2004 |accessdate=28 March 2010 }}</ref> and [[ACIIA]].<ref>{{cite news |title=L'association américaine des analystes défend sa formation |url=http://search.lesechos.fr/archives/2003/LesEchos/18863-99-ECH.htm?xtor=AL-4001 |work=[[Les Échos (France)|Les Échos]] |date=11 March 2003 |accessdate=28 March 2010 }}</ref>
SFAF plays a highly active role in the [[Euronext Paris|French financial market]]. It advises the [[Autorité des marchés financiers (France)|French financial authorities]] and assists [[List of companies of France|French listed companies]] in their dealings with the financial community. It has also established a [[code of ethics]] for the analyst profession in France.<ref>{{cite book |title=Ethique et gouvernance d'entreprises en France |last=Genaivre |first=Elisabeth |page=52 |year=2006 |publisher=Editions Publibook |isbn=978-2-7483-3216-2 }}</ref> In 1961, the Society created a professional financial training school<ref>{{cite book |title=Le monde des banquiers français au XXe siècle |last=Bonin |first=Hubert |page=171 |year=2000 |publisher=Editions Complexe |isbn=978-2-87027-778-2 }}</ref> which is now certified to issue the [[Certified International Investment Analyst]] (CIIA) diploma.<ref>{{cite book |title=Les métiers de la comptabilité et de la gestion |last=Collin |first=Claire |page=47 |year=2007 |publisher=Editions l'Etudiant |isbn=978-2-84624-757-3 }}</ref>
The society publishes ''[[Analyse Financière|Revue Analyse Financière]]'', one of Europe’s longest running financial research quarterlies, with contributions from leading academics and financial industry professionals as well as policy makers and national and international regulators.<ref>{{cite news |title=Carrefour plébiscité par les analystes financiers |url=http://search.lesechos.fr/archives/1996/LesEchos/17296-111-ECH.htm?xtor=AL-4001 |work=[[Les Échos (France)|Les Échos]] |date=18 December 1996 |accessdate=28 March 2010 }}</ref>
